Day 12 â€“ CSS Selectors

Selectors target HTML elements for styling.
Types of CSS selectors:

Element selector: p { color: red; } targets all <p> tags.

Class selector: .className { color: green; } targets elements with class="className".

ID selector: #idName { color: blue; } targets element with id="idName".
Example:

h1 { text-align: center; }
.note { font-style: italic; }
#title { font-weight: bold; }


Selectors help apply specific styling efficiently.
